<p>I'm using Telerik Radgrid for ASP.NET Ajax and programmatically adding rows to the radgrid via javascript. This is a <a href="http://docs.telerik.com/devtools/aspnet-ajax/controls/grid/data-editing/client-side-editing" rel="nofollow">well-documented approach</a> and seems to work fine on the client side. In fact javascript radgrid api calls recognized the added rows and all their values. But when I do a postback, my c# doesn't recognize any of the rows added via javascript. The c# <em>does</em> however recognize the 1 row added by default on page load. Here is my radgrid:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;telerik:RadGrid ID="RadGrid1" runat="server" AutoGenerateColumns="false" AllowSorting="false" Width="900" OnNeedDataSource="RadGrid1_NeedDataSource" OnUpdateCommand="RadGrid1_UpdateCommand"&gt;     &lt;MasterTableView DataKeyNames="ProductID" TableLayout="Fixed" EditMode="Batch" AllowAutomaticDeletes="true" AllowAutomaticInserts="true" CommandItemDisplay="Bottom"&gt;         &lt;Columns&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridBoundColumn DataField="Product" HeaderText="Product" UniqueName="Product" HeaderStyle-Width="175px" ItemStyle-Width="175px" /&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridNumericColumn DataField="QTY" HeaderText="QTY" UniqueName="QTY" HeaderStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" ItemStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" HeaderStyle-Width="60px" ItemStyle-Width="60px" /&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridNumericColumn DataField="Pretax" DataFormatString="{0:C2}" HeaderText="Pretax" UniqueName="Pretax" HeaderStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" ItemStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" HeaderStyle-Width="100px" ItemStyle-Width="100px" /&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridNumericColumn DataField="Tax" DataFormatString="{0:C2}" HeaderText="Tax" UniqueName="Tax" HeaderStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" ItemStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" HeaderStyle-Width="100px" ItemStyle-Width="100px" /&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridNumericColumn DataField="Discount" DataFormatString="{0:C2}" HeaderText="Discount" UniqueName="Discount" HeaderStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" ItemStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" HeaderStyle-Width="100px" ItemStyle-Width="100px" /&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridNumericColumn DataField="Total" DataFormatString="{0:C2}" HeaderText="Total" UniqueName="Total" HeaderStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" ItemStyle-HorizontalAlign="Left" HeaderStyle-Width="100px" ItemStyle-Width="100px" /&gt;             &lt;telerik:GridClientDeleteColumn ConfirmText="Are you sure you want to delete the selected row?" HeaderStyle-Width="35px" ButtonType="ImageButton" /&gt;         &lt;/Columns&gt;     &lt;/MasterTableView&gt;      &lt;ClientSettings AllowKeyboardNavigation="true"&gt;         &lt;ClientEvents OnBatchEditOpening="batchEditGrid" /&gt;     &lt;/ClientSettings&gt; &lt;/telerik:RadGrid&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And here is how I added rows to radgrid in javascript:</p>  <pre><code>function updateGrid() {     var tableView = $find("&lt;%=RadGrid1.ClientID%&gt;").get_masterTableView();     tableView.set_dataSource(gridArray);     tableView.dataBind();     var grid = $find("&lt;%=RadGrid1.ClientID%&gt;");     grid.repaint(); } </code></pre>  <p>This works well, the rows display in the radgrid, and telerik api functions in the js recogize the rows and values.</p>  <p>And here is where I'm trying to loop and read the radgrid values in the c#:</p>  <pre><code>foreach(GridDataItem gridItem in RadGrid1.Items) {     var sdi = new SalesDocumentItem();     sdi.IsDeleted = false;     sdi.SalesDocumentItemStatusID = (int) SalesDocumentItemStatus.NotPaid;     sdi.ProductID = Utilities.SafeInt(gridItem.GetDataKeyValue("ProductID").ToString());;     sdi.Quantity = Utilities.SafeInt(gridItem["QTY"].Text);     sdi.Amount = Utilities.SafeDecimal(gridItem["Pretax"].Text);     sdi.TaxAmount = Utilities.SafeDecimal(gridItem["Tax"].Text);     this.salesOrder.Items.Add(sdi); } </code></pre>  <p>In the loop above, no errors are thrown, but it only finds 1 record: the record loaded by default into radgrid upon page load. In fact, sometimes this record is deleted in the client side javascript, as in this case -- but new records are added via javascript. It seems that radgrid (in the codebehind) is simply ignoring everything that happened in the javascript.</p>  <p>Why is the c# not recognizing the radgrid rows added via javascript, upon postback?</p>